hopobject.body: Could I borrow your phone, please? aranleighhealthcentre.com The Porsche Boxster's power advantage is almost meaningless however, because it's far heavier than the 4C. The Porsche tips the scales at 1,320kg, while the 4C weighs a positively anorexic 985kg â a 425kg difference. Unsurprisingly then, the 4C leaves it for dead in a straight line. It'll complete 0-62mph in 4.5 seconds to the Boxster S' 5.1. The Boxster S will almost certainly claw back some of that deficit over longer sprints, and its top speed of 173mph is more impressive than the 4C's 160mph terminal velocity, but if traffic light bragging right are your thing, there is only one winner.
